        .case-study__industry-insights
            .anchor#insights
            .container
                .columns.is-variable.is-6-desktop
                    .column.is-3
                        %p.eyebrow
                            Industry Insights
                        %h3
                            Live Sports & Fan Behavior
                    .column.is-8.is-offset-1-desktop
                        .industry-insights__section
                            %p.insights-header How fans consume sports today
                            %p Sports consumption has shifted to multi-platform, always-on engagement. Fans no longer visit an event site once, they return across devices, in real time, throughout the entire tournament week.
                            .industry-insights__stats
                                .columns
                                    .column
                                        .insights-bubble.b1
                                            %p.bubble-number
                                                +34%
                                            %p.bubble-label
                                                increase in fans watching live sports on social media since 2020
                                    .column
                                        .insights-bubble.b2
                                            %p.bubble-number
                                                62%
                                            %p.bubble-label
                                                of fans discovered a new sport through short-form video
                                    .column
                                        .insights-bubble.b3
                                            %p.bubble-number
                                                70%
                                            %p.bubble-label
                                                of fans 18–34 use social media while watching sports
                            .industry-insights__bullets
                                %ul
                                    %li
                                        %span
                                            The site is a second screen.
                                        Most visitors arrive on mobile, mid-event, while watching Golf Channel. Fast load times and real-time score access were prioritized from the start of the IA.
                                    %li
                                        %span
                                            Content needs to travel.
                                        With 62% of fans discovering new events through short-form video, every content piece, from leaderboard updates to player spotlights to El 19 moments, was designed as a shareable unit, not just a page.
                                    %li
                                        %span
                                            The site is never done for the week.
                                        The architecture accounts for pre-event, during-event, and post-event states, not a single static experience.
                        .industry-insights__section
                            %p.insights-header Who the golf audience is today
                            %p Golf fans have a distinct profile that shaped content tone, navigation depth, and how the site balances premium positioning with accessibility.
                            .industry-insights__stats
                                .columns
                                    .column
                                        .insights-bubble.b4
                                            %p.bubble-number
                                                74%
                                            %p.bubble-label
                                                of pgatour.com visitors are male, but the audience is diversifying rapidly
                                    .column
                                        .insights-bubble.b5
                                            %p.bubble-number
                                                28%
                                            %p.bubble-label
                                                of on-course golfers are people of color in 2024, a record high
                                    .column
                                        .insights-bubble.b6
                                            %p.bubble-number
                                                3×
                                            %p.bubble-label
                                                more likely to have household income over $100K
                            .industry-insights__bullets
                                %ul
                                    %li
                                        %span
                                            The audience expects premium quality.
                                        Golf fans skew high-income and are accustomed to well-produced digital experiences. A generic event site template would register as low-effort to this specific audience.
                                    %li
                                        %span
                                            The sport is diversifying and the site should reflect that.
                                        Record women and BIPOC participation in 2024 means the "Open for everyone" positioning is not just a tagline. The visual language, photography direction, and content tone need to back it up.
                                    %li
                                        %span
                                            Bilingual is non-negotiable. 
                                        The local Puerto Rican audience is Spanish-dominant, the diaspora is bilingual, and the tourist audience is English-first. The site needs to serve all three without making any group feel like an afterthought.
                        .industry-insights__section
                            %p.insights-header Online ticketing behavior
                            %p Ticketing is the primary conversion goal of the site. Understanding how and when fans decide to buy shaped the homepage hierarchy, navigation, and how early the site needs to be informative.
                            .industry-insights__stats
                                .columns
                                    .column
                                        .insights-bubble.b1
                                            %p.bubble-number
                                                40%
                                            %p.bubble-label
                                                of sports fans prefer digital booking expecting a frictionless mobile flow
                                    .column
                                        .insights-bubble.b2
                                            %p.bubble-number
                                                \-50%
                                            %p.bubble-label
                                                drop in last-minute ticket buyers between Jan 2023 and Jan 2025
                                    .column
                                        .insights-bubble.b3
                                            %p.bubble-number
                                                2×
                                            %p.bubble-label
                                                more likely for live event attendees to engage with branded on-site experiences
                            .industry-insights__bullets
                                %ul
                                    %li
                                        %span
                                            The site needs to convert early, not just during tournament week.
                                        Fans are buying months out. Ticket CTAs, pricing tiers, and key event information are visible and functional from the moment the site goes live.
                                    %li
                                        %span
                                            Tier clarity drives conversion. 
                                        40% of fans prefer digital booking, but only if the flow is frictionless. Clear ticket options, transparent pricing, and a seamless handoff to purchase were treated as core UX requirements.
                                    %li
                                        %span
                                            In-person attendees are the highest-value audience.
                                        People who show up are twice as likely to engage with branded experiences. The site's event-day experience, maps, schedules, El 19 info, and QR access, was designed for this segment specifically.
                        .industry-insights__section
                            %p.insights-header Personalization & experience expectations
                            %p Fans arrive at an event site with a specific purpose. The local fan wants logistics. The tourist wants the full picture. The diaspora viewer wants the score. A good experience means none of them have to look hard.
                            .industry-insights__stats
                                .columns
                                    .column
                                        .insights-bubble.b4
                                            %p.bubble-number
                                                70%
                                            %p.bubble-label
                                                of fans say enhanced digital experiences keep them more engaged with an event
                                    .column
                                        .insights-bubble.b5
                                            %p.bubble-number
                                                62%
                                            %p.bubble-label
                                                of fans prefer events that offer personalized interactive digital experiences
                                    .column
                                        .insights-bubble.b6
                                            %p.bubble-number
                                                90%
                                            %p.bubble-label
                                                of venue-attending fans who go online rely on cellular not venue Wi-Fi
                            .industry-insights__bullets
                                %ul
                                    %li
                                        %span
                                            Three audiences, three entry points.
                                        The local fan needs parking and El 19 schedules. The golf tourist needs course info and hotel packages. The diaspora viewer needs the live leaderboard. The IA was built so each finds what they need without friction.
                                    %li
                                        %span
                                            Event-day mobile performance is the most critical moment.
                                        Nearly all connected fans at the venue use cellular. Asset optimization, load speed, and lightweight page weight were treated as design requirements.
                                    %li
                                        %span
                                            Better UX is a measurable outcome.
                                        70% of fans say digital experience quality directly affects how engaged they stay with an event. This is the quantitative argument for investing in the design, as it has a documented impact on fan retention.
        .case-study__competitive-audit
            .anchor#audit
            .container   
                .columns.is-variable.is-6-desktop
                    .column.is-3
                        %p.eyebrow
                            Competitive audit
                        %h3
                            Analogous References
                    .column.is-8.is-offset-1-desktop    
                        %p With no direct competitors, the audit benchmarks three groups: Caribbean PGA events with similar market positioning, PGA Tour sites with strong digital execution, and Puerto Rico's own sports and tourism digital presence as a tonal and visual reference.
                        %p Across all sites, a few patterns emerge clearly. The sites that work best treat their charity and community mission as a primary brand story. Bilingual support is uniformly underexecuted across the golf tournament sites. The best sites stay editorially active year-round rather than only coming alive during tournament week. The fan experience and logistics content (maps, parking, what to bring, El 19 equivalent) is consistently underdesigned relative to its importance as a day-of use case. And every site in this list, with the exception of Discover Puerto Rico, has a visual identity that is functional but not distinctive. There is a real opportunity for the PR Open to be the most visually ownable event site in this comparison set.
