                .competitive-audit__analysis
                    .analysis__tier-1  
                        %p.tier-title   
                            Tier 1 — Caribbean PGA events
                        .columns
                            .column
                                .analysis__card
                                    .card-top
                                        .card-label.coral
                                            %p Weakest reference
                                        %p.card-title Corales Puntacana Championship
                                        %p.card-subtitle Dominican Republic
                                        %p.card-text
                                            Lives as a subpage of the resort website. Minimal structure, dated design and no bilingual support. The fan experience, community programming, and charitable impact of the event are essentially invisible on the site. The tournament is treated as a resort amenity rather than a standalone brand.
                                    .card-takeaway
                                        %p
                                            %span Takeaway:
                                            A tournament this significant needs its own identity, separate from the host property.
                            .column
                                .analysis__card
                                    .card-top
                                        .card-label.green
                                            %p Best structure
                                        %p.card-title Butterfield Bermuda Championship
                                        %p.card-subtitle Bermuda
                                        %p.card-text
                                            The cleanest, most consistently maintained site in the group. The design is functional but not particularly distinctive. Clear navigation, with dedicated nav items and subpages for the charity section, fan experience page, and tournament map. The ticket flow breaks to a separate shop, creating an avoidable UX gap. There is no bilingual support.
                                        .card-takeaway
                                            %p
                                                %span Takeaway:
                                                Charity and fan experience deserve their own nav items, not subpages buried under event info.
                            .column
                                .analysis__card
                                    .card-top
                                        .card-label.blue
                                            %p Best Mission Framing
                                        %p.card-title Sony Open in Hawaii
                                        %p.card-subtitle Hawaii, USA
                                        %p.card-text
                                            Leads with its identity as a charity event, $26M raised for 350+ nonprofits is the homepage headline. Friends of Hawaii Charities is a top-level nav item. The photography is warm, community-forward, and feels genuine rather than generically tropical. Sustainability page. Slightly dated design but excellent content strategy.
                                    .card-takeaway
                                        %p
                                            %span Takeaway:
                                            Mission-forward framing makes the event feel bigger than the sport itself.
                    .analysis__tier-2 
                        %p.tier-title   
                            Tier 2 — Caribbean PGA events
                        .columns
                            .column
                                .analysis__card
                                    .card-top
                                        .card-label.green
                                            %p Best overall
                                        %p.card-title WM Phoenix Open
                                        %p.card-subtitle Arizona, USA
                                        %p.card-text
                                            The benchmark. Strong editorial identity, comprehensive logistics, and charity foregrounded at every level. "Greatest Show on Golf" branding is consistent throughout. The site also handles the event lifecycle well: it stays active year-round with construction updates, charity news, and community content rather than going dark between tournaments.
                                    .card-takeaway
                                        %p
                                            %span Takeaway:
                                            Editorial commitment and a strong brand voice make for a great site that is more than just functional.
                            .column
                                .analysis__card
                                    .card-top
                                        .card-label.yellow
                                            %p Solid Community Model
                                        %p.card-title Travelers Championship
                                        %p.card-subtitle Connecticut, USA
                                        %p.card-text
                                            Comprehensive navigation. Strong charity integration. The site does a good job of communicating the community fabric of the event, which is the Travelers Championship's core identity. Clean but unremarkable design, and adequate mobile experience. Ticketmaster handoff is clean, and a tee time lookup tool serves fans well during tournament week.
                                    .card-takeaway
                                        %p
                                            %span Takeaway:
                                            Local identity and national credibility can coexist with the right content framing and structure.
                            .column
                                .analysis__card
                                    .card-top
                                        .card-label.teal
                                            %p Premium design reference
                                        %p.card-title The Players Championship
                                        %p.card-subtitle Florida, USA
                                        %p.card-text
                                            The highest design quality of any PGA Tour event site. Clean editorial layout, dedicated Plan Your Visit section, hole-by-hole course guide, hospitality inquiry flow, and champion history archive. Charity presence is minimal relative to its budget, but the UX execution is the standard to aim for.
                                    .card-takeaway
                                        %p
                                            %span Takeaway:
                                            Every section should feel intentionally designed rather than just populated with content.
                    .analysis__tier-2 
                        %p.tier-title   
                            Tier 3 — Puerto Rico references
                        .columns
                            .column
                                .analysis__card
                                    .card-top
                                        .card-label.green
                                            %p Gold Standard
                                        %p.card-title Discover Puerto Rico
                                        %p.card-subtitle discoverpuertorico.com
                                        %p.card-text
                                            Navigation is organized around travelers needs. Best bilingual execution of any site reviewed with persistent EN/ES toggle switching the full site including navigation and CTAs. Photography is warm, human, and culturally specific. The Live Boricua campaign uses local voices to tell the island's story from the inside, the most relevant brand model for the PR Open's community-forward positioning.
                                    .card-takeaway
                                        %p
                                            %span Takeaway:
                                            The PR Open should feel like it belongs in the same visual and tonal family as this site.
                            .column
                                .analysis__card
                                    .card-top
                                        .card-label.purple
                                            %p Local sports tone reference
                                        %p.card-title Cangrejeros de Santurce
                                        %p.card-subtitle cangrejeros.net
                                        %p.card-text
                                            Owned by Bad Bunny, Noah Assad, and Jonathan García since 2021, the Cangrejeros are the most culturally relevant active sports brand in Puerto Rico right now. Fully Spanish-first, community-forward in tone, and heavy on news and roster updates. Most useful as a reference for how Puerto Rican sports fandom sounds and feels in digital spaces.
                                    .card-takeaway
                                        %p
                                            %span Takeaway:
                                            This is what authentic local Puerto Rican sports identity looks like online. The PR Open's Spanish-language content should borrow from this register, not just translate from the English version.
                            .column
                                .analysis__card
                                    .card-top
                                        .card-label.blue
                                            %p Best bilingual golf reference
                                        %p.card-title Latin America Amateur Championship
                                        %p.card-subtitle laacgolf.com
                                        %p.card-text
                                            The most polished bilingual golf tournament website in the Latin American market. Strong editorial design, live leaderboard, player profiles with national flags, video replays, and a dedicated championship section. Handles the Spanish/English balance without making either feel secondary.
                                    .card-takeaway
                                        %p
                                            %span Takeaway:
                                            The closest example of what a well-resourced bilingual golf tournament site looks like. The leaderboard, player profiles, and video integration are all worth studying directly.
        .case-study__user-research
            .anchor#users
            .container
                .columns.is-variable.is-6-desktop
                    .column.is-3
                        %p.eyebrow
                            Audience research
                        %h3
                            Understanding the Audience
                    .column.is-8.is-offset-1
                        %p Without formal user interviews, audience segments were built from PGA Tour fan demographics, Puerto Rico's official visitor profile, and the PR Open's own public-facing messaging. Four distinct groups emerged, each arriving at the site for different reasons and needing different things from it.
                        .user-research__user-bubble-wrapper
                            .user-research__user-bubble.green
                                .columns.is-gapless
                                    .column.is-3
                                        .user-bubble__user
                                            %p.user-bubble__title
                                                Local Puerto Rican fans
                                            %p.user-bubble__label.green
                                                On-Island
                                            %p.user-bubble__number
                                                3.3M
                                            %p.user-bubble__description
                                                Island residents, Spanish-dominant
                                    .column.is-9
                                        .user-bubble__user-description
                                            %p.user-bubble__sub-title
                                                What they need
                                            %ul
                                                %li.green Ticket pricing and purchase, especially day passes
                                                %li.green El 19 food, music, and entertainment schedule
                                                %li.green Parking, gates, and logistics in Spanish
                                                %li.green Rafa Campos updates and local player coverage
                                            .user-bubble__takeaway
                                                %span Design implication:
                                                Bilingual from the start, mobile-first, El 19 as a primary content section not buried under Event Info.
                            .user-research__user-bubble.blue
                                .columns.is-gapless
                                    .column.is-3
                                        .user-bubble__user
                                            %p.user-bubble__title
                                                Golf tourists flying in
                                            %p.user-bubble__label.blue
                                                Off-Island
                                            %p.user-bubble__number
                                                2,500+
                                            %p.user-bubble__description
                                                hotel nights booked per tournament, majority from US mainland
                                    .column.is-9
                                        .user-bubble__user-description
                                            %p.user-bubble__sub-title
                                                What they need
                                            %ul
                                                %li.blue Course details, player field, and tournament format
                                                %li.blue Hotel packages and Hyatt Regency information
                                                %li.blue Things to do on the island before and after rounds
                                                %li.blue Travel logistics: SJU airport, driving, shuttles
                                            .user-bubble__takeaway
                                                %span Design implication:
                                                Premium destination framing, a robust Plan Your Visit section, and photography that sells the island as much as the tournament.
                            .user-research__user-bubble.coral
                                .columns.is-gapless
                                    .column.is-3
                                        .user-bubble__user
                                            %p.user-bubble__title
                                                Diaspora fans watching remotely
                                            %p.user-bubble__label.coral
                                                Remote
                                            %p.user-bubble__number
                                                5.8M
                                            %p.user-bubble__description
                                                Puerto Ricans on the US mainland
                                    .column.is-9
                                        .user-bubble__user-description
                                            %p.user-bubble__sub-title
                                                What they need
                                            %ul
                                                %li.coral Live leaderboard and real-time score access
                                                %li.coral Broadcast schedule for Golf Channel, NBC Sports App
                                                %li.coral Rafa Campos coverage and milestone moments
                                                %li.coral Shareable highlights and social-ready content
                                            .user-bubble__takeaway
                                                %span Design implication:
                                                Leaderboard accessible from every page during tournament week, bilingual content, emotional storytelling that connects this audience to home.
                            .user-research__user-bubble.purple
                                .columns.is-gapless
                                    .column.is-3
                                        .user-bubble__user
                                            %p.user-bubble__title
                                                Sponsors, media and press
                                            %p.user-bubble__label.purple
                                                Institutional
                                            %p.user-bubble__number
                                                25hrs
                                            %p.user-bubble__description
                                                Golf Channel broadcast coverage
                                    .column.is-9
                                        .user-bubble__user-description
                                            %p.user-bubble__sub-title
                                                What they need
                                            %ul
                                                %li.purple Press credential application and media contact
                                                %li.purple Downloadable press releases and official assets
                                                %li.purple Sponsor partner information and hospitality options
                                                %li.purple Sponsorship inquiry path for prospective partners
                                            .user-bubble__takeaway
                                                %span Design implication:
                                                A clear institutional navigation path that does not interfere with the fan-facing experience, something separate but accessible.
        .case-study__problem-statement
            .anchor#problem
            .container
                .columns
                    .column.is-3
                        %p.eyebrow
                            Problem Statement
                        %h3
                            The Design Opportunity
                    .column.is-8.is-offset-1-desktop
                        %p The Puerto Rico Open is the only PGA Tour event in the Caribbean outside the Dominican Republic, hosted on an island with 5.8 million people in its diaspora, a world-class golf course, and 17 years of community investment behind it. None of that is visible in the current digital experience. The design opportunity was to build a site that reflects the scale of the event and the culture behind it. One that works as a live event hub for local fans on the ground, a destination showcase for golf tourists flying in, and a connection point for diaspora fans watching remotely from the mainland. All while giving the local Puerto Rican identity, community, and pride that surround the tournament the visibility they have always deserved.
        .case-study__main-concerns
            .anchor#concerns
            .container
                .columns
                    .column.is-3
                        %p.eyebrow
                            Main concerns
                        %h3
                            Challenges & Constraints
                    .column.is-8.is-offset-1-desktop
                        .main-concerns__concerns-wrapper
                            %p These four challenges shaped every major design decision in the project, from the information architecture to the content strategy to the visual language.
                            .columns.is-multiline.is-variable.is-8-desktop
                                .column.is-6
                                    .main-concerns__concerns-box
                                        .concerns-box__img-wrapper
